<p><strong>Photos:</strong> Upload at least 20 photos. Include your mobile locksmith van, team in uniform, completed jobs (with permission), your license, and your storefront if you have one. Businesses with 100+ photos get 520% more calls than average.</p>
<h3>Posting on GBP Weekly</h3>
<p>Google Business Profile posts keep your listing active and signal relevance. Post at least once per week. Use a <a href="/best/gbp-management-tools/">GBP management tool</a> to schedule posts ahead of time.</p>
<h2>On-Page SEO for Locksmith Websites</h2>
<p>Most locksmith websites fail at <a href="/glossary/on-page-seo/">on-page SEO</a>. They have a homepage, a contact page, and maybe one "services" page listing everything. That structure cannot rank for specific queries.</p>
<h3>Build Dedicated Service Pages</h3>
<p>Create one page for every core service. Each page needs:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] A unique title tag with the service name and primary city (under 60 characters)</li>
<li>[ ] A <a href="/blog/write-meta-descriptions/">meta description</a> that includes the service, city, and a call-to-action</li>
<li>[ ] An H1 that matches the target keyword: "Lock Rekey Service in [City]"</li>
<li>[ ] 500-800 words of unique content explaining the service</li>
<li>[ ] A click-to-call button above the fold</li>
<li>[ ] <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">Schema markup</a> for LocalBusiness and Service types</li>
</ul>
<h3>Build Location Pages</h3>
<p>If you serve 8 cities, build 8 location pages. Each page should include:</p>
<ul>
<li>The city or neighborhood name in the title, H1, and throughout the copy</li>
<li>A Google Maps embed showing your service area</li>
<li>Response time estimates for that area ("Average response time to downtown [City]: 18 minutes")</li>
<li>Testimonials from customers in that area</li>
<li>Local landmarks or neighborhoods you serve</li>
</ul>
<p>Avoid thin location pages. Each location page needs at least 300 words of unique content.</p>
<h3>Internal Linking Structure</h3>
<p>Every service page should link to related services. A "deadbolt installation" page links to "lock rekey" and "smart lock installation." Strong <a href="/blog/internal-linking-blog-posts/">internal linking</a> distributes ranking power across your entire site. Check our full <a href="/blog/on-page-seo-guide/">on-page SEO guide</a> for the complete checklist.</p>
