<h2>Local SEO and Ranking in the Map Pack</h2>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Local SEO ranking factors for locksmiths showing relevance, distance, and prominence" src="/images/blog/locksmith-seo-local-factors.webp" /></p>
<p>The Google Map Pack shows 3 local results with a map at the top of local searches. For "locksmith near me," the map pack gets the majority of clicks. Our <a href="/blog/local-seo-guide/">local SEO guide</a> covers the fundamentals. Here is how to apply them to a locksmith business.</p>
<h3>The 3 Ranking Factors</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Relevance</strong>. How well your GBP matches the search query</li>
<li><strong>Distance</strong>. How close you are to the searcher</li>
<li><strong>Prominence</strong>. How well-known and trusted your business is online</li>
</ol>
<p>You cannot control distance. But you can maximize relevance and prominence.</p>
<h3>NAP Consistency Across the Web</h3>
<p><a href="/glossary/nap/">NAP</a> stands for Name, Address, Phone number. Your NAP must be identical everywhere it appears online.</p>
<p>Audit your listings on these platforms:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Google Business Profile</li>
<li>[ ] Yelp</li>
<li>[ ] Apple Maps</li>
<li>[ ] Bing Places</li>
<li>[ ] Facebook Business Page</li>
<li>[ ] Angi (formerly Angie's List)</li>
<li>[ ] HomeAdvisor</li>
<li>[ ] BBB (Better Business Bureau)</li>
<li>[ ] ALOA directory (Associated Locksmiths of America)</li>
<li>[ ] State locksmith association directories</li>
</ul>
<p>Use <a href="/best/local-seo-tools-for-small-business/">local SEO tools</a> to scan for inconsistencies across 50+ directories at once.</p>
<h3>Building Local Citations</h3>
<p>A <a href="/glossary/citation/">citation</a> is any online mention of your business NAP. Citations on locksmith-specific directories carry more weight than generic ones.</p>
<p><strong>High-value locksmith citations:</strong>
- ALOA member directory
- Your state locksmith licensing board
- Local Chamber of Commerce
- HomeAdvisor / Angi
- Thumbtack
- Nextdoor Business Page</p>
<h3>Google Local Services Ads and SEO Together</h3>
<p>Google LSA for locksmiths places a "Google Guaranteed" badge on your listing. LSA and organic SEO work together. LSA covers the top of the page. Organic SEO covers the map pack and the 10 blue links below. Owning both spots doubles your visibility.</p>
<p>The LSA verification process also helps legitimate locksmiths. Google requires background checks, license verification, and insurance proof. Scam locksmiths cannot pass this screening.</p>
