<h2>Reviews, Trust, and Fighting Locksmith Scams</h2>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Trust signals for locksmith websites showing license, ALOA, bonded, BBB, and Google Guaranteed" src="/images/blog/locksmith-seo-trust-signals.webp" /></p>
<p>The locksmith industry has a unique problem that most SEO guides ignore entirely. Fake locksmith listings flood Google Maps, operate bait-and-switch pricing, and dispatch unqualified technicians. Google removed 10,000 fake locksmith listings and sued an alleged scam network, but the problem persists.</p>
<p>This means legitimate locksmiths must work harder to prove their credibility online. Reviews are the frontline defense.</p>
<h3>Why Reviews Are Your Best Weapon Against Scammers</h3>
<p>86% of consumers read online reviews before choosing a locksmith. Fake locksmith operations rarely have genuine reviews. They operate under disposable business names and rotate listings. A legitimate locksmith with 200+ real reviews and detailed responses stands out immediately.</p>
<h3>How to Generate Reviews Consistently</h3>
<p>Asking for reviews must be part of every completed service call. Your technician should request a review before leaving the job site.</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Send an automated SMS with a direct review link within 1 hour of service completion</li>
<li>[ ] Include a review request card in your invoice</li>
<li>[ ] Follow up with an email 24 hours later</li>
<li>[ ] Use a <a href="/tools/review-request-generator/">review request generator</a> to create templates</li>
</ul>
<p>Target 10 to 20 new <a href="/glossary/google-reviews/">Google reviews</a> per month. Use a <a href="/tools/review-response-generator/">review response generator</a> to respond to every review within 24 hours.</p>
<p>Read our full guide on <a href="/blog/get-more-google-reviews-local-business/">getting more Google reviews</a>.</p>
