<p><strong>What are the best keywords for a locksmith website?</strong></p>
<p>Emergency and location keywords drive the most calls. "Locksmith near me," "24 hour locksmith [city]," "car lockout service," and "lock rekey service [city]" have the highest conversion rates. Build dedicated pages for each service and each city you cover.</p>
<p><strong>How do I rank my locksmith business on Google Maps?</strong></p>
<p>Optimize your Google Business Profile with accurate categories, complete service listings, and 20+ photos. Build <a href="/glossary/citation/">citations</a> on 40+ directories with consistent <a href="/glossary/nap/">NAP</a> information. Generate 10+ Google reviews per month. Post weekly updates on GBP. These actions combined push you into the local pack within 3 to 6 months.</p>
<p><strong>How do I compete with fake locksmith listings on Google?</strong></p>
<p>Report fake listings through Google Maps. Verify your business through Google LSA to earn the "Google Guaranteed" badge. Build a review volume that scam operators cannot match. Display your state license number, ALOA membership, and insurance documentation prominently.</p>
<p><strong>Do locksmiths need a blog for SEO?</strong></p>
